article.description: Shawn Occeus scored 24 points with four 3-pointers, Vasa Pusica added 17 points with three treys and Northeastern drained 12 of 25 from long range to defeat Towson 80-75 Thursday night.
article.headline: Occeus scores 24 to lead Northeastern past Towson 80-75
article.linkText: Occeus scores 24 to lead Northeastern past Towson 80-75
article.story:
BOSTON -- Shawn Occeus scored 24 points with four 3-pointers, Vasa Pusica added 17 points with three treys and Northeastern drained 12 of 25 from long range to defeat Towson 80-75 Thursday night, pushing its win streak to six games and securing its second-place finish in the Colonial Athletic Association.

The Huskies (20-9, 13-4) close out the regular season Saturday at Elon, and have earned a bye into the quarterfinals of the CAA tournament March 4.

Maxime Boursiquot and Occeus wrapped back-to-back layups around a Boursiquot steal to claim a 36-34 lead for Northeastern at the start of the second half and Donnell Gresham Jr. nailed a 3-pointer for a 42-36 Huskies lead.

Justin Gorham scored nine of his career-high 28 points in the last four minutes, bringing Towson as close as 71-68. Occeus hit a 3 and Bolden Brace made four of six free throws to close it out.

Brace and Gresham scored 10 each for Northeastern. Zane Martin and Eddie Keith II scored 11 apiece for Towson (18-12, 8-9).
